#Drinkinghelps – but how, exactly? .
.
Every bottle of #Lemonaid sold supports development projects in the regions where our ingredients are grown – in Asia, Africa and Latin America. In this way, we raised more than 3 million euros for charitable purposes.
.
.
Projects are chosen and mentored by the Lemonaid and ChariTea Foundation. The goal is to help those in disadvantaged regions help themselves. The list of symptoms is often long – chronic underpayment, child labour, environmental pollution and destruction of species diversity, human rights abuses and discrimination against minorities, corrupt elites – and many more.
.
.
We believe that these problems can only be solved by the autonomous actions of local people.The Lemonaid & ChariTea Foundation therefore concentrates on increasing their resources. Thus, the organisation mainly supports entrepreneurs and educational institutes which aim to provide sustainable sources of income.

Greetings from South Africa!

We’re right now on a project trip to the home of the organic lemons that are responsible for that extra freshness of our lemonades.
Here, fruits normally get picked in April, but we were lucky to experience an intermediate harvest. Every fruit gets collected by hand. That's why about three times more people per hectare work at an organic farm than at a conventional one.

DAY 8 of our project trip to Paraguay 2016:

Besides the dinner our unique friend Rodrigo celebrated his birthday and it once more came clear, that without him the whole trip would have been different and by far not so rich in lessions and outcome. Man! You really saved us from bad experiences and pushed us into the greatness of this country and his people. We can't thank you enough for this! #love #DrinkingHelps and #RodrigoHelps

Foto: ©: Kevin McElvaney

DAY 8 of our project trip to Paraguay 2016:

It is time to say good-bye to some of our team-members and all the lovely people we met on our trip. Representatives and family-members followed our invitation that night and the Lemonaid-crew created a great fusion of the local 'Asado' and the german BBQ with unknown salads and deserts for our guests. Prost and Salut!

Foto: ©: Kevin McElvaney

DAY 8 of our project trip to Paraguay 2016:

We also had a spontaneous get together with Jose Manuel Gomez, a former worker for Fairtrade in Paraguay. We spoke about the Fairtrade system and the aim of Lemonaid to do even more for the local farmers and their families.

Foto: ©: Kevin McElvaney
#lemonaid #charitea#projecttrip#paraguay #2016 #organic#fairtrade#travel #journey#documentary#drinkinghelps#trinkenhilft#searchingforsugarmen

DAY 8 of our project trip to Paraguay 2016:

We leave his house and take a lunch-break together at one of the vegan restaurants in Asunción. Yes: this trend also reached Paraguay and if you ever visit this city, please stop by at LA Vida Verde or Pink Cow, where we had lovely food during our stay!

Foto: ©: Kevin McElvaney

#lemonaid #charitea#projecttrip#paraguay #2016 #organic#fairtrade#travel #journey#documentary#drinkinghelps#trinkenhilft#searchingforsugarmen

DAY 8 of our project trip to Paraguay 2016:

Another surprise is to see a well sorted and packed library for his various projects and investigations.
It seems as if this man never sleeps, even if he admits, that some files can't be handled by him. They give him nghtmares and remind him of his 3 year-long torture in Argentina in the 70's.

Foto: ©: Kevin McElvaney
#lemonaid #charitea#projecttrip#paraguay #2016 #organic#fairtrade#travel #journey#documentary#drinkinghelps#trinkenhilft#searchingforsugarmen

DAY 8 of our project trip to Paraguay 2016:

Another idea and dream of Martín Almada is to solve nutrition-problems for pupils in Paraguay.
One possible solution could be to dry local fruits and distibute them. His inspiration came from the german 'Studentenfutter', which he loves.

Foto: ©: Kevin McElvaney

#lemonaid #charitea#projecttrip#paraguay #2016 #organic#fairtrade#travel #journey#documentary#drinkinghelps#trinkenhilft#searchingforsugarmen

DAY 8 of our project trip to Paraguay 2016:

Next we will get a tour around his space, which displays prototypes and possible soultions for problems in Paraguay and around the world.
For example ideas to safe people from dengue fever and as seen in the picture solar solutions for energy and cooking. Some of these ideas come from him, some are a cooperation with international corporations and NGOs.

Foto: ©: Kevin McElvaney

#lemonaid #charitea#projecttrip#paraguay #2016 #organic#fairtrade#travel #journey#documentary#drinkinghelps#trinkenhilft#searchingforsugarmen

DAY 8 of our project trip to Paraguay 2016:

Martín Almada likes to joke around and entertains the whole group. He was well prepared for our visit and expected a 'big-old german', after he read about the idea and business behind Lemonaid & ChariTea, but was quite surprised to see a young and motivated group and co-founder sitting in his beautiful livingroom.

Foto: ©: Kevin McElvaney

#lemonaid #charitea#projecttrip#paraguay #2016 #organic#fairtrade#travel #journey#documentary#drinkinghelps#trinkenhilft#searchingforsugarmen

DAY 8 of our project trip to Paraguay 2016:

The last day of our official project-trip started with a smiling face opening the gate to his house, museum and 'science center'. It is Martín Almada, human rights activist and Winner of the prestigious Right Livelyhood Award. Quite a surprise to see such a positive and powerful man in the age of almost 80 years, especially when you read about his history of abduction and torture in the 70's - but it won't be the only surprise... Foto: ©: Kevin McElvaney

This fisher is doing what almost everybody in Paraguay does: carrying his mate tea and some hot or cold water with him.

DAY 2 of our project trip to Paraguay 2016:

We escape the city: A boat brings us to the countryside. On the way, Rodrigo provides us with a lot of background information about the region.
This place is called chaco-i, where people in former times had their summer residency. Today, there is not much left of that, but it offers a beautiful view on the city
Foto: ©: Kevin McElvaney

#lemonaid #charitea #projecttrip #paraguay #2016 #organic #fairtrade #drinkinghelps #trinkenhilft #searchingforsugarmen

DAY 1 of our project trip to Paraguay 2016:

One of our main to-do's today was to visit and feel the capital city of Paraguay while walking on foot.
Despite its obvious economic problems, the city has been a beautifully interesting & welcoming gateway for our project travel.
The locals kept on chatting with and smiling at us - even when we totally messed up the traffic by driving into the wrong direction for example.

Foto: ©: Kevin McElvaney

#lemonaid #projecttrip #paraguay #2016 #organic #fairtrade #drinkinghelps #trinkenhilft #searchingforsugarmen

DAY 1 of our project trip to Paraguay 2016:

Just a month ago, the @latidoamericano festival took place here in Asunción, Paraguay.
Since then many wonderful large-scale graffities cover the walls of the old-city and we were surprised by this modern and international vibe of this quarter.

Foto: ©: Kevin McElvaney

#lemonaid #projecttrip #paraguay #2016 #organic #fairtrade #drinkinghelps #trinkenhilft #searchingforsugarmen

DAY 1 of our project trip to Paraguay 2016:

Our Friend Rodrigo (left) became an essential part and qualified himself as unique cityguide and connector to the locals in Asunción.
His whole family treated us very nice and give us an easy dive into the climate and time-difference over here in Paraguay. Here you see him hanging out with one of the guys we met around Plaza Uruguaya, near the former Presidential Palace in Asunción.

Foto: ©: Kevin McElvaney
